# Jekyll + Chirpy + GitHub Pages: Images

## Image Display (in post content)

Always use inline Markdown images:

```markdown
![Alt text](/assets/img/posts/image-name.jpg)
_Optional caption_
```

## Social Media Preview (Open Graph / Twitter Card)

**For GitHub Pages compatibility**, add meta tags in `_includes/metadata-hook.html`:

```html
{% if page.url contains 'your-post-slug' %}
  <meta property="og:image" content="https://tangbyron.github.io/assets/img/posts/image-name.jpg">
  <meta name="twitter:image" content="https://tangbyron.github.io/assets/img/posts/image-name.jpg">
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Your post description">
  <meta name="twitter:description" content="Your post description">
{% endif %}
```

**Why this approach?**
- GitHub Pages rejects custom front matter fields like `og_image`
- URL-based conditional meta tags work reliably on GitHub Pages
- Must use absolute URLs (not relative paths) for Twitter/X

## Image Optimization

- Resize to max 1800px width
- Convert to JPEG at 85% quality
- Target: <500KB for hero images
- Store in: `/assets/img/posts/`
